  "extraHighlightWords": [],
  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Saturday. Mom announced we had a whole list of errands to run, and I got recruited as her official assistant for the day.",
      "zh": "星期六。媽媽宣布我們今天有一整串雜事要跑，而我被徵召成為她今天的正式助手。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Our first stop was the bank, where Mom needed to enter a small deposit into my new savings account from a few weeks ago.",
      "zh": "我們第一站是銀行，媽媽要幫我把幾週前開的新儲蓄帳戶存入一小筆錢。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The line moved slower than expected, and by the time we reached the counter, I had already read every poster on the wall twice.",
      "zh": "排隊的速度比預期慢，等我們終於輪到櫃檯的時候，我已經把牆上每張海報都看過兩遍了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Next was the post office, where Mom bought a small stamp for a letter to my grandmother's old friend, who still prefers actual mail over texting.",
      "zh": "接下來是郵局，媽媽買了一張小郵票，要寄一封信給我阿嬤的老朋友，那位朋友到現在還是喜歡真正的信件，不喜歡傳訊息。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Some people never really adapt to instant messages,\" Mom said. \"For them, a real stamp still means someone took real time and effort.\"",
      "zh": "「有些人始終沒有真正習慣即時訊息，」媽媽說：「對他們來說，一張真正的郵票，代表有人花了真正的時間和心力。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "After the post office, we walked past a small bookstore, and Mom let me go inside for ten minutes while she finished one more errand nearby.",
      "zh": "郵局之後，我們經過一間小書店，媽媽讓我進去待十分鐘，她自己去附近再處理一件事。"
    },
    {
      "en": "I found a shelf of poetry, one thin book of short stories, and a very old book about the history of our own city that nobody had checked out in years.",
      "zh": "我找到一整排詩集、一本薄薄的短篇小說，還有一本關於我們這座城市歷史、多年沒人借出過的舊書。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The bookstore owner, an older man reading quietly behind the counter, recommended a novel he said had \"an excellent, honest voice,\" whatever that meant exactly.",
      "zh": "書店老闆是位安靜坐在櫃檯後看書的老先生，他推薦了一本他說「聲音誠實又出色」的小說，我其實不太確定這句話的意思。"
    },
    {
      "en": "We ended our errands at a small cafe, where Mom ordered coffee and let me pick anything from the menu, an offer I took very seriously.",
      "zh": "我們最後在一間小咖啡館結束了今天的雜事，媽媽點了咖啡，讓我從菜單裡隨便挑，這個提議我可是非常認真看待。"
    },
    {
      "en": "I chose a hot chocolate that arrived far too hot to drink immediately, forcing me to wait, staring at it with great patience I did not actually feel.",
      "zh": "我點了一杯熱到根本沒辦法馬上喝的熱可可，只好乾等，表面上耐心地盯著它，內心其實一點都不耐煩。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mom used the quiet moment to ask about school, my friendships, and whether I had considered what subject I might want to focus on later.",
      "zh": "媽媽利用這段安靜的時間，問了我學校的事、我的友誼，還有問我有沒有想過以後想專注在哪個科目上。"
    },
    {
      "en": "I admitted I still had no clear answer, and she said that was completely fine at my age, and possibly even fine at her age too.",
      "zh": "我坦承自己還沒有明確的答案，她說在我這個年紀完全沒關係，甚至她這個年紀可能也還是沒關係。"
    },
    {
      "en": "On the walk home, we passed a small shop selling barbecue skewers, and the smell alone was enough to convince Mom to buy a few for tonight's supper.",
      "zh": "回家的路上，我們經過一間賣烤肉串的小店，光是聞到味道就足以說服媽媽買幾串當今晚的晚餐。"
    },
    {
      "en": "By the time we got home, my legs felt heavier than my school bag, but the whole day had felt oddly satisfying in a quiet, ordinary way.",
      "zh": "等我們到家的時候，我的腿感覺比我書包還重，但整天下來，卻有種安靜、平凡又莫名讓人滿足的感覺。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Lesson of the day: a day full of small errands sounds boring on paper, but somehow it turned into one of my favorite Saturdays this whole year.",
      "zh": "今日心得：一整天都是些小雜事，寫在紙上聽起來很無聊，但不知怎麼地，這變成了我今年最喜歡的星期六之一。"
    }
  ],
